int a = 5; //stack allocated variable

int *ptr; //declares a pointer

//1 Step Version
int *ptr = new int; //actually allocates the memory for the integer in the heap

//2 Step Version
int *ptr;
*ptr = new int;

//how to remove a pointer
delete ptr;

//LINKED LISTS
A way to link objects together. Could be a series of numbers, each object point to the next.


